# ============================================================================
# There is intentionally NO backend-local env file here.
#
# The backend reads its runtime config (DATABASE_URL, SESSION_SECRET, JWT_SECRET,
# S3_*, REDIS_URL, …) from the MONOREPO ROOT — `swat/.env.local` — because NestJS'
# ConfigModule is pointed there (`envFilePath: [… '../../.env.local']`). One file
# serves the whole stack, and `scripts/start.sh` exports it to the web too.
#
# (Next.js, by contrast, can only auto-load from its own app dir, so the web keeps
#  its own `apps/web/.env.local`.)
#
# Set up (from the repo root `swat/`):
#   cp .env.example .env.local                                 # backend + shared runtime config
#   cp apps/backend/prisma/.env.example apps/backend/prisma/.env  # DATABASE_URL for the Prisma CLI
#   # …or just run ./scripts/setup.sh, which does both (+ install + DB).
#
# Run the backend on its own (from the repo root `swat/`):
#   docker compose --env-file infra/docker-compose.env up -d   # Postgres/Redis/MinIO
#   pnpm --filter @swat/backend run db:migrate                 # apply migrations
#   pnpm --filter @swat/backend run db:seed                    # demo data (optional)
#   pnpm --filter @swat/backend dev                            # watch mode on $BE_PORT (default 3000)
#
# Full guide: apps/backend/README.md.
# ============================================================================
